              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "15 micro-g/cm2 of 93% enriched U-235 electro-",
                "deposited on gold(17 micro-g/cm2) and resin(10 micro-g/",
                "cm2) coated VYNS plastic film(45 micro-g/cm2)"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "COINC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Fast coincidence between two fission",
                "        fragment detectors. Each run using fast",
                "        neutrons was preceded and followed by a",
                "        run using neutrons thermalised by passage",
                "        through 7 cm of polyethylene."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SOLST"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Two solid-state surface barrier detectors"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "-Light and heavy fragment distribution for the thermal",
                " runs preceding and following each fast run were fitted",
                " with gaussian curves. Average channel width in energy",
                " units was determined from the known difference between",
                "the light and heavy fragment average kinetic energies",
                "in thermal fission of U-235.",
                "-The difference between the average of the fast pulse",
                " height sum distribution and the average of the",
                " preceding and following thermal sum distributions was",
                " converted to energy units using the above calibration."
              ]
            }
          ],
